<br>
The point is that some people are frustrated because they enjoyed PoG as an xp zone, a zone to make some pp, and to get some decent gear with a small force.  It had turned into more like the PoP zones where people could solo or duo and casual players and groups of a few friends could go.  Those people, those who don't have big guilds and time for big raids, but who play casually with a few friends, those kinds of people are upset, and I don't blame them.<br>
<br>
I enjoyed the PoG's when we used to have to time them.  I hated them sometimes when we wiped and had to deal with them during CR's.  But they were a part of PoG.  But honestly, PoG was better without the PoG's chasing you down.<br>
<br>
There is a major major weakness in Everquest and that weakness is that it's very difficult to gear up at all if you play casually and with just a small group of friends.  If you are a hard-core player who raids all the time with a good-sized guild it's no problem, the game is made for you.  PoG was a place where the casual player could gear up with some decent gear, not great, but decent.  <br>
<br>
In my opinion there needs to be more quests in Everquest and more content that smaller groups can do to gear up.  Sure, a raid force of 30-40 should be able to get much better gear than a group of five, but there should be some longer quests that group of five can do to get some gear or some mobs they can kill.  PoG was such a place but with the change it is no longer that type of zone. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=taelenskychaser>Taelen Skychaser</A> at: 4/24/03 12:09:07 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rombusmindspire>Rombus Mindspire</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Administrator</span><br>  Posts: 6820<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/24/03 12:17:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26229.topic&index=39>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.tritonguild.com/rombus/sidepic.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Whine over PoG</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Yes, and 5 months ago most of the people in my guild didn't have AAskills, MGB, and had lots of Kunark armor. And on my very crowded server Kael is highly contested. We still don't have anyone with MGB. And I still wear one piece of crafted armor on my warrior.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
